==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bewilderment
<hw>Be*wil"der*ment</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The state of being bewildered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bewildering tangle or confusion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He . . . soon lost all traces of it amid <qex>bewilderment</qex>
of tree trunks and underbrush.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bewinter</ent>⟦br⟧
